-- Spain, Portugal Tied 0-0 After 15 Minutes at World Cup Match in Cape Town
-- Alex Duff
-- 2010-06-29T19:00:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/spain-portugal-tied-0-0-after-15-minutes-at-world-cup-match-in-cape-town.html

          
          
             Spain and Portugal were tied 0-0
after 30 minutes of a World Cup round-of-16 game in Cape Town,
South Africa.  
 The winner will play Paraguay in the quarterfinals.
Paraguay beat Japan 5-3 on penalty kicks earlier today.  
          
          


  


        